Fix for imaginecolor::__tpString() not returning valid hex colors as not zero padding. Eg: its hex representation of 0 is single 0 - fine when you have 3 zeros, but if you have one of the other channels with a 2 digit hex value, you get a 4/5 digit hex code, which gives weird results when passed on to imagick (i am using it with drawer::text ).With fix to force sprintf to pad, it works as expected.rnrnEasy to reproduce:rnrnecho new ImagineColor('00ff00');rnrnExpected: #00ff00rnGot: #0ff0rnrnWorks with fix.

Add docblocks to all classes and interfacesThis is need to work around a PHP bug resulting in a (random?)ndocblock being returned when calling getDocComment() on a classnreflection of a class that has no docblock.nnSee PHP bug 55156. Although reported to be fixed as of 5.3.7 thentest for the bug fails in 5.3.8 (for 5.4.0 the test passes).nnThe bug then causes errors to be reported by Doctrine's annotationnreader, because it sees annotations on classes that don't haventhem, and thus lack needed use statements. Bummer.n
